  "currentAcceptance": [
    "Production SettlementEngineModule binds a complete PostgreSQL repository directly; RuntimeCore, optional Prisma, repository factory, ActionExecutor memory authority and process-memory OutboxService are absent from the production settlement graph.",
    "Production startup fails closed when the payment repository mode is missing, memory or unknown.",
    "All payment, beneficiary, bank-operation, hold, release, refund, reconciliation and ledger reads/mutations execute in trusted server-derived RLS transactions.",
    "Every human actor, including ADMIN and SUPPORT_MANAGER, requires an exact active DealParticipant row; only the cryptographically bound BANK_CALLBACK actor has a narrow system exception.",
    "Financial HTTP mutations require recent server-derived MFA and reject absent, stale, future or client-header-only evidence.",
    "Money is stored and calculated only as integer minor units; no float or amountRub authority remains.",
    "Confirmed money counters can change only by the exact amount and type of one validated PENDING bank operation in the same callback transaction.",
    "Payment terms and release basis are versioned PostgreSQL facts linked to the canonical Deal.",
    "Reserve and release requests atomically commit payment state, bank operation, audit and PENDING outbox; only an authenticated verified bank callback can confirm money movement.",
    "Partial payouts, holds, refunds and beneficiary allocations cannot over-release, become negative or exceed the confirmed reserve.",
    "Callbacks, reconciliation and mutation commands are durably idempotent, optimistic-concurrency protected and safe across restart and multiple API instances.",
    "Same-tenant outsiders and cross-tenant users are denied under restricted PostgreSQL principals.",
    "No live bank, nominal-account or money-movement claim is introduced.",
